  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7114 sitting right at the max negative gamma strike of 7115, dealers are currently buying the dip as hedging flows support this level. The thick positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5341M) should provide strong support below, while the massive gamma concentration at 7150 (+6716M) and especially 7200 (+8328M) will act as significant resistance on any bounce attempt. In this PIN regime with total GEX at 64B+, expect dealers to fade moves away from current levels, creating a mean-reverting environment with 7100-7150 as the likely trading range.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to bounce off current levels and chop between 7100-7150.",
